cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.CR 

The paper proposes a method that combines one-class support vector machine (OC-SVM) with autoencoder and random Fourier features to improve the scalability and interpretability of anomaly detection. This involves deep learning techniques such as stochastic gradient descent and representation learning architecture, which are commonly associated with the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also evaluates the method on image datasets, which suggests a potential association with cs.CV (Computer Vision). Additionally, the use of random Fourier features and optimization complexity may relate to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), respectively.
